3. Problem Statement Development
Project Title
E-Book Management System

Problem
Traditional book management systems and unorganized digital collections make it difficult for users to search, access, and manage books efficiently. Physical storage limitations, poor categorization, manual record-keeping, and security risks further reduce the effectiveness of existing solutions.

Solution
The proposed E-Book Management System provides a centralized digital platform that allows users to store, organize, search, and access e-books easily. It also includes administrative features for managing digital resources and implementing secure authentication.

Target Users
Students
Educators
Academic institutions
Administrators

Value Proposition
The system improves accessibility, enhances resource organization, strengthens security, and simplifies digital book management while supporting modern learning needs.
